Four persons died while three others sustained injuries in a lone accident on Sunday at Nami village, Agai Local Government Area of Niger. The Sector Commander of the FRSC in Niger, Mr Kumar Tsukwam, told the News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) in Minna on Monday that the accident occurred at about 10 pm on Sunday night. He said that an articulated vehicle was loaded with chemicals with 49 male   passengers seating on top from Lagos, heading to Kano State. ” Forty nine male persons were involved in the accident; four of them died, while three others sustained injuries and 42 escaped unhurt. “The injured victims were rescued and taken to Lapai General Hospital, while the dead were deposited at the same  hospital mortuary in Lapai.’’ (NAN) 